// Single source of truth for user-facing AI model entries.
//
// Each entry is identified by its `id` (`recommended`, `frontier:anthropic`,
// `frontier:openai`, `balanced`, `balanced:anthropic`, `balanced:xai`, `fast`,
// `fast:google`). A bare
// tier id like `balanced` is the tier's default backing model; ids of the
// form `<tier>:<provider>` pin that tier to a specific provider. When a
// pinned id is removed, `resolveModelId` falls back to the bare tier default.
// The
// `gatewayModelId` is the bare upstream slug used by the AI gateway
// (e.g. `anthropic/claude-opus-4.8`). The agent-gateway adds any proxy
// prefix when forwarding to the runner.
//
// All ids are aggregate roles that resolve to a concrete provider
// internally, so cron jobs and saved defaults can pin a *role* instead of a
// specific weights revision and survive model upgrades without migration.

